00:04:04.920 --> 00:04:08.880
Now, you may be saying, "Yeah, yeah&nbsp;
Starla. I've heard all this before,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:08.880 --> 00:04:13.980
but if Disney cares so much, why do so many&nbsp;
people get away with selling these products on&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:13.980 --> 00:04:16.980
Etsy - and why isn't Etsy&nbsp;
doing anything about it?"

00:04:16.980 --> 00:04:19.560
Let's start with a bit of IP law 1-0-1.

00:04:19.560 --> 00:04:24.600
It's important to note that only the owner of&nbsp;
a copyright can report infringement of said&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:24.600 --> 00:04:30.120
copyright. Etsy does not own Disney, which means&nbsp;
that in order to legally remove these items from&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:30.120 --> 00:04:34.140
the platform under infringement of intellectual&nbsp;
property, Disney has to report them. And they do.

00:04:34.140 --> 00:04:36.900
And while it may not seem&nbsp;
like anything is being done,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:36.900 --> 00:04:42.000
shops get shut down all the time for&nbsp;
copyright infringement on Etsy. In fact,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:46.200
it's one of the most common questions I see in&nbsp;
my inbox from sellers who have had their shops&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:46.200 --> 00:04:50.820
shut down - and as much as I wish I could&nbsp;
help them, you cannot get your shop back,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:50.820 --> 00:04:55.980
or even a buyer account back, if you get&nbsp;
caught for copyright infringement on Etsy.

00:04:55.980 --> 00:05:00.840
Not to mention, Disney isn't blind to this issue.&nbsp;
In fact, they have a team of lawyers dedicated to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:00.840 --> 00:05:05.040
watching businesses who violate their IP. And&nbsp;
just like the couple we talked about earlier,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:05.040 --> 00:05:08.280
often Disney's legal team will&nbsp;
watch these businesses over time,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:08.280 --> 00:05:13.380
taking action once they've noticed that the&nbsp;
seller is making a lot of money from their IP.

00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:18.300
So, as you've probably guessed already if&nbsp;
you're one of those sellers who sits on Etsy&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:18.300 --> 00:05:22.080
all day reporting Disney listings,&nbsp;
you're likely wasting your time.

00:05:22.080 --> 00:05:27.840
But, if you want to clue Disney in on a case of&nbsp;
infringement, you can always email them directly.&nbsp;

00:05:27.840 --> 00:05:29.940
You know.
If you're feeling spicy.

00:05:29.940 --> 00:05:35.100
Just be aware that in the realm of copyright&nbsp;
infringement, parody is its own thing and is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:35.100 --> 00:05:40.200
protected by law. Which is why the movie Blood&nbsp;
and Honey, a Winnie the Pooh horror satire coming&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:40.200 --> 00:05:44.700
out this February, is able to exist without&nbsp;
issue from Disney. Though, if you're selling on&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:44.700 --> 00:05:49.800
Etsy specifically, they will almost always&nbsp;
side with the IP holder. So if a larger&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:49.800 --> 00:05:54.660
company tries to flag you for infringement on a&nbsp;
satirical item, you'll likely still get a strike.

00:05:54.660 --> 00:05:58.800
Every time I make a video about copyright&nbsp;
that states the laws and facts, I get a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:58.800 --> 00:06:02.220
ton of hate in the comments from people&nbsp;
who either don't like the laws or who&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:02.220 --> 00:06:06.780
don't agree with them. But not liking the laws&nbsp;
doesn't exempt you, and as a business coach,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:06.780 --> 00:06:11.160
my job is to keep you informed and&nbsp;
safe. Not to blow smoke up your butt.

00:06:11.160 --> 00:06:15.300
Way back when I first started selling on Etsy&nbsp;
at age 19, I didn't know these laws either,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:15.300 --> 00:06:18.240
and I had a few listings taken down&nbsp;
for copyright infringement as well.&nbsp;

00:06:18.240 --> 00:06:20.700
It's a common mistake but one that you have to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:20.700 --> 00:06:23.940
correct quickly once you realize&nbsp;
that it's a mistake you're making.

00:06:23.940 --> 00:06:28.560
The bottom line is, if it's okay for us,&nbsp;
as small sellers to steal - what makes it&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:28.560 --> 00:06:33.900
not okay for big businesses to steal from us?&nbsp;
The laws can't be made in a way that makes it&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:33.900 --> 00:06:38.940
totally okay for the lesser party to use another&nbsp;
company's IP, but not the other way around. There&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:38.940 --> 00:06:43.980
has to be a line somewhere, and those lines are&nbsp;
subjective based on who draws them in the sand.

00:06:43.980 --> 00:06:49.500
It's either all okay or none of it is okay, which&nbsp;
means as sellers, we need to be aware of the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:54.780
